    %p 
      The sphere of technology in Andalusia is undergoing a rapid development stage: there are 11 technology parks and 8 technical universities in the territory of the autonomous community; more than 1.5 thousand companies operate in the sphere of ICT. There are representative offices of such market giants as IBM, Microsoft, Oracle, Ericsson, Fujitsu and others. Andalusia is the national leader as far as the spread of 3G internet is concerned. There is also a well-developed motor way and railway network and regular air connection with Russian and European capitals. 
    %p 
      %span The stimulating policy of the Andalusian authorities, clearly interested in cooperation with investors and full of ambition to host IT projects, is the key to the intensive development of the oldest European start-up community in the region. The members of the community gladly share their experience during numerous events that take place here all year round. This is why Andalusia is a perfect location for hosting a business accelerator camp and putting your project into action. You will have anything you might need for productive work, efficient studying and fun in your free time.
